               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Naghāʼim al-ashvāq by Farīd Muḥammad Sardar</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85024485 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85129660 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh97006785" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1001A-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on the religious aspects of music (samāʻ) and its use in Sufi ritual, by Farīd known as Muḥammad Sardar who would appear to be a member of the Chishti order.</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into 36 sections (naghmah).</p>
                        <p>ff. 85; end defective; 15 lines per page; nastaʻliq; rubrications; worm-eaten; 17th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8033">Farīd Muḥammad Sardar</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8033">فرید محمد سردار</persName>
